joke_list.joke: A blind man walks into a bar. And a table. And a chair.
You'll never guess who I bumped into on the way to the opticians! Everyone.
What do you get when you mix human DNA with goat DNA? Kicked out of the petting zoo.
Did I tell you about my new job at the circus? My job is to circumcise the elephants. The pay isn't great, but the tips are enormous.
What's better than winning the silver medal at the Paralympics? Having legs.
Two fish in a tank, one says to the other; 'You man the guns, I'll drive!'
Why do you never see hippos hiding in trees? Because they're very good at it.
Why did the half-blind man fall into a well? He couldn't see that well.
Why doesn't blind people clean up after their guide dogs' mess? Because they can't see shit.
My dad asked me the other day: 'Are you even listening to me?' Which is a really weird way to start a conversation if you ask me.
I stand corrected, said the man in the orthopedic shoes.
My dog is a rescue, which is a really self-righteous way of saying I bought a used dog.
I love telling jokes about the Titanic; they always go down well. A great way to break the ice.
2 fish in a tank; one turns to the other and says: 'do you know how to drive this thing'?
Why do flamingos stand on one leg? Because if they lifted both, they'd fall over.
My grandfather has the heart of a lion and a lifetime ban from the zoo.
I want to die peacefully in my sleep like my grandfather did, not screaming in terror like the passengers in his car.
A snake walks into a bar, and the bartender asks: 'how?'
If life gives you lemons, make lemonade. If life gives you melons, you might be dyslexic.
What do you call a dog with no legs? You don't call it, you go get it.
My wife comes to me and says 'Honey, I don't understand the concept of human cloning.' I said 'That makes two of us.'
What do you call an indecisive bee? A maybee.
What do you call an American bee? A USB.
What did the blind carpenter say when he picked up sandpaper? What the heck did I just read!
How many therapists does it take to change a light bulb? One - but the light bulb has to want to change.
Why is there no pregnant Barbie? Because Ken came in another box.
What were Michael Jackson's pronouns? He/he.
Why can't you trust atoms? They make up everything.
Why don't kleptomaniacs understand metaphors? They always take things, literally.
Did you hear about the scarecrow that won the Nobel Prize? He was outstanding in his field!
Why did the skeleton go to a movie by himself? Because he had no body to go with.
Why does Santa have such a big sack? Because he only comes once a year.
What do you call a fly with no wings? A walk.
Those of you who believe in telekinesis, raise my hand.
Two cannibals side by side eating a clown. One looks at the other and says 'does this taste funny to you?'
"Your honor. If we are what we eat, then my client is an innocent man"
What do Winnie The Pooh and Jack The Ripper have in common? They got the same middle name.
What's the difference between in-laws and outlaws? Outlaws are wanted.
What's a 3-letter word that starts with gas? Car.
What did the Jedi say to the cowboy? Use the horse.
What does a deaf gynecologist do? He reads lips.
What's Mozart up to these days? Decomposing.
How close was Anakin to the lava? About two feet away.
What's orange and sounds like a parrot? A carrot.
What's brown and sticky? A stick.
What do you call a boomerang that won't come back? A stick.
What's red and smells like blue paint? Red paint.
What's the difference between swine flu and bird flu? Bird flu requires tweetment, and swine flu requires oinkment!
How do you think the unthinkable? With an iceberg.
Why do scuba divers fall backward out of the boat? Because if they fell forwards, they'd still be in the boat.
The Buddha walks up to a hotdog stand and says: 'make me one with everything.'
I took the shell off my racing snail to make it go faster. If anything, it just made it more sluggish.
What's a foot long and slippery? A slipper.
Why do Norwegian warships have a barcode on the side of them? So that they can Scandinavian.
Where did Napoleon keep his armies? In his sleevies.
Where does a pirate keep his buccaneers? Under his buccan-hat.
What has four letters, sometimes has nine, and never has five.
A sheep, a drum, and a snake fall off a cliff. Bah-dum-tss.
Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts!
What's blue but not very heavy? Light blue.
What did one snowman say to the other snowman? 'Do you smell carrots?'
What do you call a magical dog? A Labracadabrador.
What is the best time to go to the dentist? Tooth hurty.
When a Norwegian robot analyzes a bird, it Scandinavian.
What's red and bad for your teeth? A brick.
What kind of bees make milk? Boobees.
I believe a good pun is its own reword.
How tall is a spider? 8 feet.
I know a really great knock-knock joke, but someone else has to start it
I used to wear a necklace with me and my lover in it, but they left me. Now I'm independent.
What do you call a four-eyed pig? Piiiig.
What do you call a fish with no eyes? A fsh.
Why don't ants ever get sick? Because of their little antibodies.
Do you know what's not right? Left.
What goes down but doesn't come up? A yo.
If a sentence only contains a dependent clause.
Knock knock! Who's there? Spell! Spell who? W-H-O.
What did the buffalo say when his son went to college? Bison.
What did the Indian kid say to his mother when he left for his first day of school? Mumbai.
How do you make an egg roll? You push it.
Why did Adele cross the road? To say hello from the other side.
What did the pirate say when he turned 80? Ayyee Matey!
What do you call a person who steals all your toenail clippings? A cliptoemaniac.
I used to hate facial hair, but it grew on me.
What do you call a sleepwalking nun? A roamin' Catholic.
Why did the stadium get hot? All the fans left.
